    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced courgette</strong> and <strong>shallot</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> stock </strong>to the pan with your<strong> salmon flakes </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tagliatelle </strong>and your<strong> cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> to the sauce and stir everything together \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy salmon & courgette sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-courgette-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy salmon & courgette sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Season with a generous crack of <strong>black pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
